snippet.textDisplay:
"Did you ever hear of the tragedy of Huawei Mate 30?"

"No"

"I thought not. It's not a story the US government would tell you. It's a Huawei legend. The Mate 30 was a powerful phone of the Chinese, so powerful and so expensive, it could use the electricity to influence the Li-ion atoms to create, battery life. It had such  a power of the Kirin 990, it could keep the games it cared about, from lagging."

"It could actually, save games from lag?"

"The Chinese side of the world is a pathway to many phones, some consider to be, unnatural."

"What happened to it?"

It became so powerful, the only thing it was afraid of was, losing battery life, which, eventually of course it did. Unfortunately, Huawei showed the US government everything it knew, then the US government banned it in the US. Ironic, it could save others from dying (it has reverse wireless charging), but not itself."

"Is it possible to get this phone?"

"Not in the US."

(I hope I haven't offended anyone. This is just a joke)
